<exercise
	title="Encapsulation using constructors, getters, setters and other methods" 
	compulsory="no" 
	deadline="02.03.2011">

	<objectives>
		<obj>Learn about encapsulation</obj>
		<obj>Learn about constructors</obj>
	</objectives>

	<requirements>
		<req>
			Use Eclipse for writing and testing all parts of the exercise.
		</req>
		<req>
			Use the JExercise tool to verify the code.
		</req>
		<req>
			The Card and CardDeck classes must be defined/stored in package/folder oving5.card and the Person class in oving5.person. The packages card and person are subpackages of oving5.
		</req>
		<req>
			For classes; use the exact names and modifiers that are specified in the exercise.
		</req>
		<req>
			For methods, use the exact name, parameter datatype, sequence of parameters, and 
			datatype for return value that are specified.
		</req>
		<req>
			NB! Parameters and fields, and their types, are not always specified. If not, it can 
			be deduced from the text and it is a part of the exercise to figure out what it has 
			to be.
		</req>
	</requirements>

	<reading>
		<book title="Liang">
			<chapter nr="5.2">Defining a method</chapter>
			<chapter nr="5.3">Calling a method</chapter>
			<chapter nr="5.5">Passing parameters by values</chapter>
			<chapter nr="8.2">Defining Classes for Objects</chapter>
		</book>
	</reading>
	
	<comment></comment>
</exercise>
